cs.NI, cs.LG, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.AI 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on improving network access for IoT devices. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper proposes and evaluates different learning strategies based on Multi-Arm Bandit algorithms. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is relevant as the paper considers the impact of radio collisions on network access. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is relevant as the paper proposes strategies to improve the autonomy of IoT devices. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is less likely but still possible as the paper employs machine learning algorithms to improve network access.
